Title: Quantum Canonical Transformations

TheoriesAuthors: Arlen Anderson

Comments: 11 pages, Imperial/TP/92-93/20

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B305 (1993) 67-70

Two quantum theories are physically equivalent if they are related, not by aunitary transformation, but by an isometric transformation. The conditionsunder which a quantum canonical transformation is an isometric transformationare given.